    "faq": {
      "type": "brand-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does a Paslode gas nailer work?",
            "answer": "<p>Paslode nailers use a combination of a <strong>gas fuel cell</strong> and a <strong>lithium battery</strong>. The battery powers a fan and ignition system, while the gas fuel cell provides the combustion energy that drives each nail. A small internal combustion occurs with every trigger pull, firing the nail into the material. This eliminates the need for compressors, hoses or mains power entirely.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is the difference between gas cartridge and battery-only nailers?",
            "answer": "<p>Paslode's <strong>gas + battery</strong> system delivers significantly more driving power than battery-only nailers, which is why Paslode remains the professional standard for framing and structural nailing. Battery-only nailers rely solely on the battery for impact energy, which limits their power output. Paslode's gas combustion technology delivers 82J of energy in the IM350+ \u2014 enough to drive 90mm nails into softwood consistently.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Which nails are compatible with my Paslode nailer?",
            "answer": "<p>Paslode nails are <strong>purpose-built for each specific nailer model</strong>. The IM350+ uses clipped-head or full round-head framing nails (50-90mm). The IM65A uses 16-gauge angled brads (32-63mm). The IM90i uses strip nails (50-90mm). Always use genuine Paslode nails \u2014 third-party nails may cause jams, misfires and can void your warranty.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How often should a Paslode nailer be serviced?",
            "answer": "<p>Paslode recommends a <strong>full service approximately every 50,000 shots</strong>. Between services, regular cleaning of the combustion chamber and nose area will maintain performance. Paslode operates a UK service centre with nationwide collection \u2014 the standard service and repair costs \u00a3149 +VAT and includes genuine parts with a 4-month warranty on fitted components.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What warranty do Paslode nailers come with?",
            "answer": "<p>Paslode nailers come with a <strong>2-year manufacturer warranty</strong>, 90-day warranty on normal wearing parts, and <strong>5-year warranty on nylon moulded components</strong>. Register your tool on the Paslode website to activate your warranty. As an official Paslode stockist, Invicta Tools can assist with all warranty enquiries and service bookings.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you offer trade pricing on Paslode?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. We offer <strong>competitive trade pricing</strong> across the full Paslode range including nailers, nail packs, gas fuel cells and accessories. Contact our trade team on <strong>01843 593 440</strong> or email <strong>sales@invictatools.co.uk</strong> for volume discounts and trade account enquiries. Free next-day delivery on all orders over \u00a399.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
